David Ortiz  hit his 24th home run of
the season to help the Boston Red Sox break a three-game losing
streak with a 6-1 victory over the New York Yankees.  Ortiz hit a solo home run in the seventh inning yesterday
for the American League East-leading Red Sox (73-52), who are
two games ahead of the Tampa Bay Rays. The Yankees (63-59) are
in fourth place, 8 Â½ games behind the leader.  John Lackey  (8-10) allowed one run on six hits while
striking out one in 6 2/3 innings at Fenway Park in Boston.  Hiroki Kuroda (11-8) gave up five runs on 11 hits and
struck out six in the Major League Baseball contest.  To contact the reporter on this story:
